By Teniola Ibitola Lagos – An Ebute-Meta Magistrates’ Court, Lagos on Friday, ordered the remand of one Lukman Yekini in custody for allegedly having carnal knowledge of a 13-year-old girl. Yekini, whose plea was not taken, is facing a two-count charge of conspiracy to commit felony and defilement. The magistrate, Mrs A.O. Salawu,
remanded the defendant at the Ikoyi Prison pending an outcome of legal
advice from the State Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP). Earlier, the Police Prosecutor, Insp
Chinalu Uwadione, had told the court that the defendant committed the
offences sometimes in February at Block 25, Flat 2, Glover Estate,
Ebute-Meta. Uwadione alleged that Yekini had forceful sexual intercourse with the teenager. According to him, the offences violate Sections 137 and 411 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The magistrate adjourned the case until May 8 for the advice of DPP.